We’re still enjoying Christmas around here! Some years I’m already taking it down by now, others it lingers a little longer. I think it’s staying until after New Year’s this year💙Hope you’re all enjoying your holidays!
And it’s still Christmas in our home💙Hope you’re all still enjoying the blessings of the season!!🙏🏻✨

Here’s a last look at our Christmas decor this year…it will be coming down next week. I’m looking forward to a clean house! I know I certainly am grateful for so many things and I’m extremely grateful for all of you! Thank you for being here with me!
💙💙💙

Happy New Year! I hope you’ve all had an amazing holiday! We’re still in vacation mode over here, I’ll be packing up all of our Christmas decor starting tomorrow. Here’s a look back at our kitchen from last spring, some inspiration for a clean, fresh start to the New Year! I don’t know about you, but I’m so excited for what this year will bring. Every day is a gift and a blessing from God! I want to wish you all nothing but blessings and God’s favor this year. Here’s to your health, happiness, prosperity, success and so much more. If you are reading this today, you are truly blessed!💙Happy New Year my friends and all the very best in 2023!
Happy Saturday! Here’s a look back at some of my favorite shots and projects from last year💙Hope you’re all having a great start to this one! Enjoy the day everyone!

I’m hoping to update a couple of things in here this spring! Which look is your favorite and do you prefer our faux grasscloth wallpaper or paint?

Sharing this on CL Blog today! I’ve put off cleaning my silver for years until I finally tried this all-natural method:
 
➡️Line a baking dish, deep basin or sink with aluminum foil.

➡️Use equal parts baking soda and salt.

➡️Place tarnished silver in your basin or dish.

➡️Cover with boiling water.

➡️Watch the transformation in seconds!

Who says you can’t make a huge impact with a small pool???? This space was a labor of love over the past year, that was met with so many challenges - from size and placement restrictions because of our very sloped property and existing hardscaping and septic system, laws that dictated much of the design (like having to fence it in with specific placement and sizing), and doing it all on a pretty small budget. There are still parts of our yard that aren’t finished yet and will probably get done next year, but here it is! It’s modest in size, simple and minimal, beautiful and so peaceful. This is our favorite place that we’ve been hanging in this summer, when it hasn’t been raining! Stay tuned for the full blog post coming later this week, where you can get all the details. Happy Sunday!💙

Tomorrow is my 50th birthday, which is SO very surreal since I feel like I’m still 20, ha! Where do the years go??? It’s a bittersweet birthday, as I’m so very grateful to God, for every single year and all of the blessings that have come with each one. I’m so grateful for my beautiful children and my amazing husband, my siblings, family and friends…I am blessed! But I’m really missing my parents more than ever - this is a very tough one to celebrate without them💔

I decorated our home this year for Christmas, fully influenced by my beautiful Mother (who always was and always will be my style icon), as is almost everything I do. She would LOVE our home this year! Mom and Dad, I love and miss you both so much…I wish you were here celebrating my birthday, Thanksgiving, Christmas, all of it! Until we see each other again!❤️❤️❤️

I had a vision….to bring our kitchen to another level! Working with a modest budget and updating the things that made sense, our kitchen update is by far one of our favorite projects to date! It was a beautiful kitchen before - but we wanted to elevate the design and create a more custom look and feel, one that’s more personal to our style, taste and our home. We don’t have a paneled fridge, we don’t have a walk-in pantry, we don’t’ have a huge range (not going bigger was a big mistake when we built our home 14 years ago!), we don’t have a breakfast nook, and many other things you might find in a truly custom kitchen. But we do have a stunning space with incredible custom uppers with a timeless and chic trellis design, new lower drawers and paneled dishwasher custom matched to our existing lowers, all new brass hardware, a gorgeous quartz slab backsplash, new pot filler, brass rails and more! It is truly our own and we’re thrilled with the outcome! Head to CL Blog and search Kitchen Update to read all about the details and decisions, or head over from my stories or highlights.
